reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble!
reviews.reviewText: Perfect size for my office which is in the corner of my room. Enough space for laptop and dual monitor. Very strudy and great desk for the price! Would be perfect for college dorm due to small size, and shelves!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Was exactly what I was looking for!
reviews.reviewText: This is a simple yet sturdy desk. It fit perfectly in the spot I had planned to use it in. My wife likes it also.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy little desk
reviews.reviewText: Purchased this for my son for Christmas. He had it built in less than an hour. Easy setup, pretty sturdy for the money. He’s a gamer and his favorite part of this desk is the plugs on TOP!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Pretty good desk so far, everything looks nice and it fits pretty well against my wall. I thought it was going to go over my wall at first but it sits nicely. My main issue is just the instructions for building it. Not only are they just vague but they just throw the images onto you with no description for anything. Sorta like the art tutorials that show you how to draw like a lion or something but by step 2 it’s already jumped to the lion fully drawn and now you have to shade it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024

reviews.reviewText: Grreat utilitarian desk for small space. Easy Assembly and sturdy. Easily 5 star.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Tiny desk! Perfect
reviews.reviewText: Spent weeks looking for a tiny desk that could hold all my screens and have a raise section. This was perfect, easy to assemble, clear instructions, stable, and good finish.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice large desk
reviews.reviewText: This is a nice, large desk with great features, especially for students. The USB chargers are great, so is the bottle holder on the side. The desk can be assembled in two ways to make sure it fits the way you need it. Great product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: For my small house, this is the perfect size! I loved that all of screws are done with just an allen wrench.The charging station, in my opinion, should be pushed back further (like underneath the top shelf), to allow more usable space, but it’s still workable. Since one side is used for my laptop, and the other side is used for my mouse, there’s no real space for my desk organizer. However, with my side table right beside my desk, I can make that work.The instructions were confusing, at first, because they don’t give “directions”, they just give you pictures. But once my son and I studied them long enough, the assembly went very smoothly. Had all the parts, with extras just in case.Oh! I will say, though, the packaging looked like crap! Really beat up and torn. Surprisingly, everything inside was just fine.
